      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object manages a list of rules ("
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects). A rule system also offers methods for evaluating its list of rules in a context defined by two features: a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501238-state"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " dictionary containing information to be tested by rules, and a set of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501276-facts"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " representing the conclusions drawn as a result of rule evaluation. You can evaluate facts based on a binary truth state—that is, a fact either is or is not in the set—or on a continuously variable membership grade, representing different levels of veracity, confidence, or strength for use in fuzzy logic."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You construct a rule system by creating "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " objects and adding them to the system’s list of rules. There are multiple ways to construct rules: for greater reusability, use the methods listed in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule#1664637"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "; or for greater flexibility, use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule/1501102-rulewithblockpredicate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method or create a custom subclass of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gknspredicaterule"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Then, add rules to the system with the methods listed in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem#1664654"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To evaluate a system, call the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501077-evaluate"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. This method processes each rule in the system in the order it appears in the system’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501078-agenda"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " list. You set this order with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule/1501148-salience"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of each rule, or with the order in which you add rules to the system. As the system processes each rule, it tests the rule’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule/1501234-evaluatepredicatewithsystem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method to determine whether the rule is satisfied in the context of the system. If the rule’s predicate is satisfied, the system executes the rule’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrule/1501111-performactionwithsystem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method and moves the rule to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501057-executed"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " list (so the further evaluation of the agenda doesn’t repeatedly trigger the rule’s action)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Rules typically use the system’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501238-state"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " dictionary as input and its set of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem/1501276-facts"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " as output. (However, more complex systems can include sets of rules whose predicates test facts or whose actions mutate the system’s state.) After evaluating a rule system, you can examine the set of facts it has produced using the methods listed in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkrulesystem#1664883"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". You can then use the presence of a fact in the set, the value of its membership grade, or the combined membership grades of a group of facts to influence the behaviors in your game."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information about rules and rule systems, read "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "Rule Systems",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/RuleSystems.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172-CH10"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "GameplayKit Programming Guide",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/General/Conceptual/GameplayKit_Guide/index.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015172"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
